Package fr.sorbonne_u.components.hem2025e2.equipments.batteries.mil

MIL simulation models of the batteries.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BatteriesUserI
    The class BatteriesUserI defines signatures of methods that a model that represents the user of the batteries must implement to be notified when the batteries becomes empty or a minimum level is available again.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BatteriesCoupledModel
    The class BatteriesCoupledModel defines the coupled model for the batteries DEVS simulator.
    BatteriesPowerModel
    The class BatteriesPowerModel implements the simulation model for the batteries.
    BatteriesSimulationConfiguration
    The interface BatteriesSimulationConfigurationI defines configuration parameters for the batteries simulator.
    BatteriesUnitTesterModel
    The class BatteriesUnitTesterModel implements a model that executes test scenarios for the batteries.
    RunBatteriesUnitaryMILSimulation
    The class RunBatteriesUnitaryMILSimulation is the main class used to run simulations on the models of the batteries in isolation.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BatteriesPowerModel.EventToBeEmittedNext
    The enumeration EventToBeEmittedNext defines the action to be taken when the batteries has just become empty or when they are available again after they were empty.
    BatteriesSimulationConfiguration.BatteriesTestScenario
